          <div class="training-phases">
            <div class="phase-card" id="rollout-phase">
              <h4>Trajectory Rollout with Visual State Reasoning</h4>
              <div class="phase-content">
                <p>Each trajectory begins with an initial observation <span set:html="\\(o_0\\)" /> provided by the environment. The agent generates a structured output <span set:html="\\(a_t = \\langle z_t, \\bar{a}_t \\rangle\\)" />, where <span set:html="\\(z_t\\)" /> represents reasoning tokens and <span set:html="\\(\\bar{a}_t\\)" /> represents executable actions.</p>
                
                <div class="reasoning-strategies">
                  <h4 class="strategies-title">Visual State Reasoning Strategies:</h4>
                  <div class="strategy-content">
                    <div class="strategy-details" id="nothink-content">
                      <p><strong>NoThink:</strong> We train the VLM agent to generate only an executable action <span set:html="\\(\\bar{a}_t\\)" />, and the output action token <span set:html="\\(a_t\\)" /> is <code>&lt;answer&gt;</code> <span set:html="\\(\\bar{a}_t\\)" /> <code>&lt;/answer&gt;</code>.</p>
                      <div class="code-snippet">
                        <code>&lt;answer&gt;...&lt;/answer&gt;</code>
                      </div>
                      <p>Learning: <span set:html="\\(z_t = \\emptyset\\)" /></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="strategy-details" id="freethink-content">
                      <p><strong>FreeThink:</strong> We train the VLM agent to produce any form of natural language reasoning, allowing visual state reasoning to emerge without a predefined structure. The agent generates action tokens as <code>&lt;think&gt;</code> <span set:html="\\(z_t\\)" /> <code>&lt;/think&gt;</code> <code>&lt;answer&gt;</code> <span set:html="\\(\\bar{a}_t\\)" /> <code>&lt;/answer&gt;</code>.</p>
                      <div class="code-snippet">
                        <code>&lt;think&gt;...&lt;/think&gt;&lt;answer&gt;...&lt;/answer&gt;</code>
                      </div>
                      <p>Learning: <span set:html="\\(z_t \\neq \\emptyset\\)" />, and <span set:html="\\(z_t\\)" /> is natural language tokens.</p>
                    </div>
